      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SERENITY GIRL (3) hit the ground running and on speed early but faded out of it to finish fourth (22.60) at this track over 390m. Form here at the trip sound including five wins. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Looks the one to beat on her best form. ESPECIAL YOGI (8) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (22.63) at Shepparton over 390m. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Winning chance. SAINT RAINE (7) was a brilliant winner two back but last start drifted back and wound up strongly to finish a 4 length second at Warrnambool (22.55). The form out of her last race has been franked. Expecting another good run. ASTON DUNKEL (2) gets a chance to redeem an unplaced effort here last start.",
